physical_examinations.relevant_findings: At physical examination, she had no pubic hair and her breast development was Tanner stage I. Hormonal evaluation revealed low serum estrogen levels and undetectable basal serum LH and FSH.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Patient was treated with estrogen and progestin replacement, resulting in development of thelarche, pubarche, and withdrawal bleeding.
Successful pregnancy ensued after five cycles of exogenous gonadotropin injections.
